<bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
<p>The company, located in Cohoes, N.Y., was founded in 1854 to manufacture "woven goods of various kinds." It carried inventories of both cotton and wool machinery. The Cohoes Co., organized in 1826, was formed to build a
dam and power canal system on the Mohawk River at Cohoes. Most textile mills in the area purchased water-power and rented land from the Cohoes Co.</p>
</bioghist>
<scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
<p>Mohawk River Mills, Cohoes, NY. Business records, 1854-1885 (ca. 250 items).
Includes certificate of incorporation, contract to construct a factory, minutes of meetings of stockholders &amp;amp; trustees, and correspondence of Truman G. Younglove, company president. Also accounts with Cohoes Iron Foundry and Machine Shop; water rent accounts for Mohawk and for Flax Cotton Mills building; bills and receipts, production and payroll
records; inventories of stock on hand, including those for Watervliet Mills, Halcyon Mills and Atlantic Mills; and sales records and financial statements. Also a few records of Flax Cotton Mills and Harmony Mills.</p>
</scopecontent>
